		</ul>
	</objectives>
        <introduction>
                <p xml:id="find-heatwarm">Energy is a noun<idx><h>energy</h><h>noun</h></idx>; objects can <em>have</em> energy.  The <xref ref="s-kinetic-theory" text="title" /> shows us how the temperature of a gas can be an expression of the <xref ref="ss-thermal-energy" text="title">kinetic energy of the molecules of the gas</xref>.</p>

                <aside><title>Paragraph referenced by</title>
                        <p>
                        Discussions of
                                <xref ref="d-forcenoun" text="title">force as a noun</xref> and
                                <xref ref="d-heatverb" text="title">heat as a verb</xref>,
                        <xref ref="connect-friction-work" text="type-global" />
                        </p>
                </aside>
                <p xml:id="d-heatverb">Heat is a verb<idx><h>heat</h><h>verb</h></idx>; heating is a process of <em>exchanging</em> energy.  Recall our
                        <xref ref="d-forcenoun" text="title">discussions of force</xref><idx><h>force</h><h>noun</h></idx> and
                        <xref ref="d-workverb" text="title">work</xref><idx><h>work</h><h>verb</h></idx>.</p>

        </introduction>

